{"body": "<div id=\"doc-contents\" class=\"content\">\n\n  <h1>BasicScalingRule object</h1>\n  <p><p>Used in combination with user defined Scaling Metrics.</p></p>\n\n    <h2>Polymorphism</h2>\n\n    <p><em>BasicScalingRule</em> is a type that implements the <a href=\"/definitions/S/ScalingRule.html\">ScalingRule</a> type.</p>\n\n    <p>When an object of type <a href=\"/definitions/S/ScalingRule.html\">ScalingRule</a> is expected, you can use one of type <em>BasicScalingRule</em> (or use any other implementation).</p>\n\n    <h2>Abstract Type</h2>\n\n    <p><em>BasicScalingRule</em> is an abstract type. When an object of type <em>BasicScalingRule</em> is expected, you must pass an object of one of the following types:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"/definitions/S/SqsQueueSizeScalingRule.html\">SqsQueueSizeScalingRule</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/definitions/L/LoadAveragesScalingRule.html\">LoadAveragesScalingRule</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/definitions/F/FreeRamScalingRule.html\">FreeRamScalingRule</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/definitions/U/UrlResponseTimeScalingRule.html\">UrlResponseTimeScalingRule</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/definitions/B/BandWidthScalingRule.html\">BandWidthScalingRule</a></li>\n    </ul>\n\n\n\n\n  <h2>Properties</h2>\n  <table class=\"fullwidth\">\n    <thead>\n      <tr>\n        <th>property</th>\n        <th>attributes</th>\n        <th>valid values</th>\n        <th>description</th>\n        <th>filter option</th>\n      </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody>\n      <tr>\n        <td><span class=\"fixed-width\">name</span><br/><span class=\"data-type\">\n            string\n        </span></td>\n        <td><span class=\"notes\">\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip required\">required</span><br>\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip create-only\">create-only</span><br>\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip filterable\">filterable</span><br>\n        </span></td>\n        <td>\n        </td>\n        <td></td>\n        <td>\n            ?name=...\n        </td>      \n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td><span class=\"fixed-width\">ruleType</span><br/><span class=\"data-type\">\n            string\n        </span></td>\n        <td><span class=\"notes\">\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip required\">required</span><br>\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip create-only\">create-only</span><br>\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip filterable\">filterable</span><br>\n        </span></td>\n        <td>\n            <em>\"BasicScalingRule\"</em>\n        </td>\n        <td></td>\n        <td>\n            ?ruleType=...\n        </td>      \n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td><span class=\"fixed-width\">scaleDown</span><br/><span class=\"data-type\">\n            integer\n        </span></td>\n        <td><span class=\"notes\">\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip required\">required</span><br>\n        </span></td>\n        <td>\n        </td>\n        <td><p>Scale down threshold.</p></td>\n        <td>\n        </td>      \n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td><span class=\"fixed-width\">scaleUp</span><br/><span class=\"data-type\">\n            integer\n        </span></td>\n        <td><span class=\"notes\">\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip required\">required</span><br>\n        </span></td>\n        <td>\n        </td>\n        <td><p>Scale up threshold.</p></td>\n        <td>\n        </td>      \n      </tr>\n    </tbody>\n  </table>\n\n</div>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n$(function () {\n  var descriptions = {\n    \"required\": \"<i>Required</i> properties must be set when you send a <i>BasicScalingRule</i> object to the API.\",\n    \"optional\": \"You can choose wether or not to set <i>Optional</i> properties when sending <i>BasicScalingRule</i> objects to Scalr.\",\n    \"create-only\": \"<i>Create-only</i> properties are set when the object is created, but can't be modified later. They are typically allowed in POST requests but not in PATCH requests.\",\n    \"read-only\": \"<i>Read-only</i> properties are set by Scalr and can't be modified through the API. They are set when you retrieve a <i>BasicScalingRule</i> from Scalr, but you should not set them when sending <i>BasicScalingRule</i> objects to Scalr through POST or PATCH requests.\",\n    \"filterable\": \"<i>Filterable</i> properties can be used to filter the results returned by the API according to the value of these properties.\"\n  };\n  var spans = document.querySelectorAll('.need-tooltip');\n  for (var i = 0; i < spans.length; i ++) {\n    for (var cls in descriptions) {\n      var span = spans.item(i);\n      if ($(span).hasClass(cls)) {\n        new Tooltip({\n          target: span,\n          content: descriptions[cls],\n          classes: 'tooltip-theme-arrows',\n          position: 'top left'\n        });\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n});\n</script>\n", "title": "BasicScalingRule definition - Scalr API Documentation"}